HEADWORD: holocephalan
<hw>holocephalan</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A member of the
<ord>Holocephali</ord>, fish with high compressed heads and a bodies
tapering off into a long tail. See also <er>Hoocephali</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
